title: How to turn knowledge into wisdom - Quora

response.answer_text: The Wisdom's Path/ T. A. Rubinshtein Just like a scientist creates a new set of chemicals from former sets of chemicals, Just like the musician composes a new melody from the set of notes they practiced, Just like the poet evolves a poem from their set of beautiful words, Just like a military officer arranges the best cohesion of their specialties, You, the man or woman on the path of wisdom, Have the potential to devise a new plan and conclusion From the knowledge, you possess. The more knowledge you shall gather, The more wisdom you may be able to produce, And the more wisdom you produce, The more knowledge you create from it, And so you can build a wonderful symphony of never-ending cycles, Towards the goal of more and more grand truths Just by this complex yet basic resource, Called information. And, the more wisdom you produce, The happier you can turn your life into, Because wisdom grants power and control, Whether it's on your life or on other's; Use your wisdom wisely And you become even more wise, For wisdom can be infinite, And so is the capability of your inner potential, Which awaits to be optimally actualize. Analyze this poem, and become even wiser, Since even the irrelevant of information can become useful, With the power of creativity, Which is a necessity for your industry of wisdom.

Knowledge is not called knowledge unless it is used. Using it reveals an the error in our understanding of knowledge. Then we remove that error and get closer to the understanding of knowledge. Then that knowledge becomes wisdom. It's just like trying to invent something using the laws of physics. So if you don't understand the law of physics correctly, then invention is not possible. When you understand the law completely, then invention becomes possible and this is called wisdom. Wisdom is the use of knowledge in social sciences to spread the beauty of knowledge in society۔ Do remember Wisdom is like a God and is of eternal nature. If one uses it or not it is there. And if one knows it or not, it is there.

A person goes to learn Karate. Over the next few months, his master teaches him different types of blocks, kicks, punches, Kata and sparring techniques. He practices it hard and finally able to perform it with perfection and with right amount of strength. This is knowledge.  Later he remembers, what his master used to tell during every belt ceremony. ‘Karate is only for defense and self-protection. You are not supposed to misuse it to offend others or attack them for your selfish gains or pleasure.’ He follows it strictly for rest of his life. This is called Wisdom. Wisdom is when you know to differentiate between what is right and what is wrong and then use your amazing knowledge accordingly for constructive purposes, rather than destructive purpose.

response.answer_text: You acquire wisdom when you drop all the knowledge. As long as one has knowledge, one is living a dead life. By dead life, we mean that one is not able to completely look at anything with fresh eyes. Such a person would be unable to listen to anybody else because of the knowledge already within the mind interfering with the things heard. When trying to see new things, such a person will not be able to look at it with fresh eyes. He or she would be comparing, evaluating or expecting something and not just be simply observing something. Wisdom is in being able to perceive anything with total attention. A total attention is not possible with a mind full of knowledge. It is only possible when a person has dropped all the knowledge from one’s mind and has acquired a sense of equanimity towards life and the things it contains. An empty mind is wisdom

If I knew what wisdom was I might be able to answer definitively. Since I don’t, I’ll just guess that it probably has a lot to do with thinking twice (or three times) about the possible consequences and effects of what sounds at first like a really cool idea.

the wise don’t just follow the facts, but consider more than facts for action. a wise man might speak in riddle, but riddles are the only way he can convey his complexity of thought. when does knowing the value of one become wisdom? when you see that one is a relative size of measurement. when does that knowledge become wisdom? when another man understands relative size for the value of one is just a method for measuring on the need for construction of idea. when does that knowledge become wisdom? when all is known, and one dares look beyond…wisdom appears to be a rare phenomenon. if all were wise, then all would be easy, and none would be wise, but then the wise would be called stupid? if then wisdom can not be stupidity, is then the experience of freedom not wisdom itself? wisdom then appears to be seeing what others are missing. aristotle said, “it is the mark of a true intellect to entertain an idea without believing it.” i say, “it is the mark of the wise to know when to believe in and follow said idea or not.” so one definition of wisdom from me is knowing when to use knowledge, when to action, and when to believe. but also, wisdom is seeing what others are missing as you read up there.

How do you turn knowledge into wisdom? Wisdom is not an outgrowth of knowledge. It is an independent faculty that enables one to evaluate and understand the human condition/predicament under a given set of circumstances and act upon that insight/understanding. It does not depend on scientific knowledge. 1 Sept 2017

It doesn't. But you can take the knowledge and use it to become more wise because it's like a tool kind of like climbing a tree but knowledge is the tree base and stump and the wisdom is out on the leaves you can use the tree climbing up and get the leaves which are wisdom
Knowledge doesn’t become wisdom. Wisdom is an ability. Wisdom lets you do things with knowledge.

When one knows how, when and where to use their knowledge ( putting one's knowledge into use at the right time, right place and in the right manner / quantity & quality), they are known as wise ( that is when knowledge becomes wisdom)!!!!!

Utilize your knowledge on a daily basis to make good choices for your self. Learn to love yourself and then share that love with others. Knowledge is power so learn to use that power in serving others and you will find joy. Wisdom comes when you are spiritually at peace and loving others. Meaningful relationships with others add to your story and as you develop humility, God will bless you with wisdom.

Well if you were wise you wouldn’t bother. You would already know that wisdom is just knowledge about how to use knowledge wisely. You will gain wisdom through experience. It has nothing to do with knowledge or the transmutation of it.

response.answer_text: Knowledge is sought and gathered. Wisdom can only dawn! Wisdom is epiphanic in nature and, therefore, a ‘becoming’ is not possible! Immiscible!
Knowledge is a pile of facts. Wisdom is knowing how to use those facts appropriately. The difference is experience.
Knowledge becomes wisdom through rightful application. I.e. Getting the mind content (wisdom) into becoming a positive reality.

You may have great knowledge, but what good is it if it doesn’t benefit you? So this knowledge may be used in landing a job or some other situation that grants you the money you need to survive. If you land that job, your knowledge may grant you the practical wisdom to solve and keep the job!
There is only way to get wisdom is apply knowledge to real time in life .so you will get actionable wisdom.
By making safe decisions without resentment, and becoming the good person you are.
Emotional intelligence, networking and, commitment to walk the walk, not just talk the talk. Join - or start - an affinity-group. I just did - you're needed somewhere - don't delay.
The actions that advance life are loving ones. So any knowledge you can gather that helps you love more is valuable actionable knowledge.
knowledge is from man understanding and wisdom is from God, but nevertheless man occupies all.
